WEBVTT

00:00:03.103 --> 00:00:05.072
(moaning, groaning)

00:00:05.072 --> 00:00:08.342
♪

00:00:08.342 --> 00:00:11.979
Where-- where am I?

00:00:11.979 --> 00:00:13.814
Can't see a thing.

00:00:13.814 --> 00:00:16.550
♪

00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:18.085
A bump.

00:00:18.085 --> 00:00:20.754
Where'd that come from?

00:00:20.754 --> 00:00:23.223
Hm, the ground
is warm.

00:00:23.223 --> 00:00:26.894
But why is
it vibrating?

00:00:26.894 --> 00:00:28.428
A wall...

00:00:28.428 --> 00:00:30.030
(grunting)

00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.832
♪

00:00:31.832 --> 00:00:34.868
A handle-- is this
some kinda door?

00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:36.970
(grunting with effort)

00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:43.911
♪

00:00:43.911 --> 00:00:44.945
Okay.

00:00:44.945 --> 00:00:47.581
It's dark,
it's shaking...

00:00:47.581 --> 00:00:50.050
I must be in the
back of a truck.

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:54.321
♪

00:00:54.321 --> 00:00:56.223
Well, this
can't be good.

00:00:57.090 --> 00:01:03.297
♪

00:01:03.297 --> 00:01:06.333
♪ Going fast makes
me feel alive ♪

00:01:06.333 --> 00:01:09.369
♪ My heart beats
in hyper drive ♪

00:01:09.369 --> 00:01:12.506
♪ Do you think you can
win only if I lose ♪

00:01:12.506 --> 00:01:15.242
♪ Just let
destiny choose ♪

00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:17.878
♪ I can hear
you breathing ♪

00:01:17.878 --> 00:01:20.480
♪ I can see
you coming ♪

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:26.420
♪ I can feel the wind
that's blowing me around ♪

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:29.690
♪ Take a shot at me
running side by side ♪

00:01:29.690 --> 00:01:32.359
♪ It's a blur
as I go by ♪

00:01:32.359 --> 00:01:34.895
♪ I can hear
you breathing ♪

00:01:34.895 --> 00:01:37.598
♪ I can see you coming ♪

00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:42.803
♪ I can feel the wind
that's blowing me around ♪

00:01:42.803 --> 00:01:45.606
♪ See the sun a risin' ♪

00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:48.308
♪ Fire in the sky ♪

00:01:48.308 --> 00:01:53.280
♪ Greatness thrusts
itself into our lives ♪ ♪

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:56.516
♪

00:01:58.518 --> 00:02:02.422
At least my eyes are
adjusting to the dark.

00:02:02.422 --> 00:02:03.724
Is that... ?

00:02:03.724 --> 00:02:06.593
♪

00:02:06.593 --> 00:02:09.029
What is my Duel Runner
doing here?

00:02:09.029 --> 00:02:11.732
This morning, I-- I was
contacted by someone

00:02:11.732 --> 00:02:14.001
who needed some parts
replaced on a practice

00:02:14.001 --> 00:02:15.535
module or something.

00:02:15.535 --> 00:02:17.771
So I made
a house call...

00:02:17.771 --> 00:02:20.107
Right, I remember now.

00:02:20.107 --> 00:02:24.578
When I got there, something
just didn't seem right.

00:02:24.578 --> 00:02:28.415
(man inside)
Help, somebody
help me!

00:02:28.415 --> 00:02:30.884
-Aagh!
-Ah!

00:02:30.884 --> 00:02:31.718
Hello?

00:02:31.718 --> 00:02:35.422
♪

00:02:35.422 --> 00:02:36.790
Hey, are you okay?

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:38.291
Mister!

00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:42.295
(man)
Get him, boys!

00:02:42.295 --> 00:02:43.130
(heavy thudding)

00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:44.164
It was a trap...

00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:46.133
But why, what do
they want from me?

00:02:46.133 --> 00:02:48.135
(man)
<i>A reasonable question.</i>

00:02:48.135 --> 00:02:51.738
<i>I'm glad to see you finally</i>
<i>woke up, Mister Fudo.</i>

00:02:51.738 --> 00:02:54.741
<i>I trust you're finding your</i>
<i>accommodations pleasant.</i>

00:02:54.741 --> 00:02:56.777
<i>Did you notice the</i>
<i>mint on your pillow?</i>

00:02:56.777 --> 00:02:58.345
Who are you people?

00:02:58.345 --> 00:03:00.580
(man)
<i>Oooh... we're just a nice</i>
<i>bunch of citizens</i>

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:03.750
<i>devoted to social justice</i>
<i>and family values.</i>

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:06.453
Not quite the vibe I got from
those thugs at the house.

00:03:06.453 --> 00:03:07.454
<i>Oh, them?</i>

00:03:07.454 --> 00:03:09.423
<i>We employ some</i>
<i>rough types.</i>

00:03:09.423 --> 00:03:11.158
<i>It keeps 'em off</i>
<i>the streets.</i>

00:03:11.158 --> 00:03:12.626
What do you
want with me?

00:03:12.626 --> 00:03:15.262
<i>I can see that you're not</i>
<i>interested in a sarcastic</i>

00:03:15.262 --> 00:03:18.298
<i>tête-à-tête, so I'll cut</i>
<i>to the proverbial chase.</i>

00:03:18.298 --> 00:03:21.234
<i>You're an incredible</i>
<i>Turbo Duelist, Yusei.</i>

00:03:21.234 --> 00:03:23.036
<i>So I'm sure you're</i>
<i>already aware</i>

00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:25.906
<i>that the World Racing Grand</i>
<i>Prix is fast approaching.</i>

00:03:25.906 --> 00:03:27.808
<i>I'm putting together</i>
<i>a team to compete</i>

00:03:27.808 --> 00:03:29.176
<i>and I want you on it.</i>

00:03:29.176 --> 00:03:30.444
Oh, yeah?

00:03:30.444 --> 00:03:32.846
Well, thanks, but I'm
afraid I'm not available.

00:03:32.846 --> 00:03:35.882
I've already formed a team
with my friends Jack and Crow,

00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:39.052
so if you could just pull over
and let me out, that'd be great.

00:03:39.052 --> 00:03:41.088
<i>Ha ha ha.</i>

00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:44.257
<i>You will be joining my team</i>
<i>one way or another, kid.</i>

00:03:44.257 --> 00:03:46.259
<i>You can either sign up</i>
<i>voluntarily or we can</i>

00:03:46.259 --> 00:03:48.361
<i>take you to see</i>
<i>our Psychiatrist.</i>

00:03:48.361 --> 00:03:50.764
<i>He's got a fascinating way</i>
<i>with people's minds,</i>

00:03:50.764 --> 00:03:52.332
<i>although he's a bit</i>
<i>of a control freak,</i>

00:03:52.332 --> 00:03:53.767
<i>if ya know</i>
<i>what I mean.</i>

00:03:53.767 --> 00:03:56.937
Listen, buddy, I'm getting
a little tired of your jokes.

00:03:56.937 --> 00:03:58.438
<i>You think I'm joking?</i>

00:03:58.438 --> 00:04:01.074
<i>You really don't wanna</i>
<i>mess with me, my friend!</i>

00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:04.778
<i>I am not exactly what you would</i>
<i>call a well-balanced person.</i>

00:04:06.513 --> 00:04:07.948
I can see that.

00:04:07.948 --> 00:04:12.319
<i>Now please just sit back, relax</i>
<i>and enjoy the view, Yusei,</i>

00:04:12.319 --> 00:04:16.957
<i>because you aren't going</i>
<i>anywhere-- Ha ha ha!</i>

00:04:17.491 --> 00:04:21.962
♪

00:04:25.198 --> 00:04:31.772
♪

00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:34.107
(man)
<i>Are you sure you</i>
<i>looked everywhere?</i>

00:04:34.107 --> 00:04:35.408
Like Oil Slick Alley?

00:04:35.408 --> 00:04:36.910
Pier 23?

00:04:36.910 --> 00:04:38.645
If you're so
worried about Yusei,

00:04:38.645 --> 00:04:40.180
why don't you
go look for him?

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:42.682
I would, but Cluckers
Deep Fried Chicken

00:04:42.682 --> 00:04:44.117
doesn't deliver itself.

00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:45.752
I'm on the clock.

00:04:45.752 --> 00:04:48.255
(Jack)
<i>I tried that Ultra Crispy</i>
<i>Crisper the other day.</i>

00:04:48.255 --> 00:04:49.356
<i>It's a little heavy</i>
<i>on the paprika,</i>

00:04:49.356 --> 00:04:50.590
<i>but otherwise,</i>
<i>I thought it--</i>

00:04:50.590 --> 00:04:53.660
How are you talking about
fast food right now?

00:04:53.660 --> 00:04:54.995
What if Crow's
right and something

00:04:54.995 --> 00:04:57.798
awful's happened
to Yusei?

00:04:57.798 --> 00:04:59.132
Man, these yahoos.

00:04:59.132 --> 00:05:00.867
I'm sure Yusei's okay.

00:05:00.867 --> 00:05:03.270
So he didn't call Crow
back, no big deal.

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:05.472
Well, actually,
it's not just that.

00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:08.708
I also got this really
weird message at the garage.

00:05:08.708 --> 00:05:11.111
(man)
<i>Your friend Yusei Fudo</i>
<i>has been taken.</i>

00:05:11.111 --> 00:05:12.679
<i>I thought you</i>
<i>should know.</i>

00:05:12.679 --> 00:05:15.315
(Akiza)
<i>What-- Why are you just</i>
<i>now telling us this?</i>

00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.850
I didn't wanna
freak anyone out.

00:05:16.850 --> 00:05:19.286
(Akiza)
<i>I am gonna cobble you</i>
<i>when I see you.</i>

00:05:19.286 --> 00:05:21.488
I believe you mean
clobber, Akiza.

00:05:21.488 --> 00:05:23.156
To cobble is
to make a shoe.

00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:25.625
(Akiza)
<i>Well, whatever, then</i>
<i>I'm gonna cobble up some</i>

00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:28.595
<i>boots and use 'em to</i>
<i>kick Crow's butt!</i>

00:05:28.595 --> 00:05:30.730
This Yusei thing's
got you going.

00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:32.365
If didn't know any
better, I'd say that

00:05:32.365 --> 00:05:33.333
you were in love
with him...

00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:34.868
<i>Stop right</i>
<i>there, Jack!</i>

00:05:34.868 --> 00:05:36.203
All I'm saying is...

00:05:36.203 --> 00:05:37.204
Hmm.

00:05:37.204 --> 00:05:38.572
All you're saying
is what, Jack?

00:05:38.572 --> 00:05:40.807
What's goin' on?
There's an
interference signal.

00:05:40.807 --> 00:05:44.077
Like someone's trying to
hack into the transmission.

00:05:44.077 --> 00:05:46.613
(man)
<i>If you can hear this,</i>
<i>the vehicle carrying Yusei</i>

00:05:46.613 --> 00:05:48.949
<i>is a soda delivery</i>
<i>truck traveling north</i>

00:05:48.949 --> 00:05:52.419
<i>on Blue Hill Ave</i>
<i>in Crescent Valley.</i>

00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:54.521
You need to stop that
vehicle and rescue him

00:05:54.521 --> 00:05:56.756
before it reaches
its destination.

00:05:56.756 --> 00:05:59.059
Who are you?
Identify yourself.

00:05:59.059 --> 00:06:01.528
This channel is reserved
for sector security.

00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:04.564
(man)
<i>Time is wasting.</i>

00:06:04.564 --> 00:06:06.066
What should we do?

00:06:06.066 --> 00:06:07.267
You heard him.

00:06:07.267 --> 00:06:08.335
Move it!

00:06:08.335 --> 00:06:14.741
♪

00:06:14.741 --> 00:06:19.179
Well, we've just
entered Crescent Valley.

00:06:19.179 --> 00:06:21.214
My arm's burning.

00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:22.949
Yusei must
be close by...

00:06:22.949 --> 00:06:32.692
♪

00:06:32.692 --> 00:06:34.094
There it is.

00:06:34.094 --> 00:06:36.496
Get us down there on
Irving, Mina, quick!

00:06:36.496 --> 00:06:38.198
I saw a soda
delivery truck.

00:06:38.198 --> 00:06:41.201
♪

00:06:41.201 --> 00:06:43.970
(tires screeching)

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:48.308
♪

00:06:48.308 --> 00:06:49.943
(moaning in pain)

00:06:49.943 --> 00:06:51.144
We're getting closer.

00:06:51.144 --> 00:06:52.712
(Mina)
Is that the truck?

00:06:52.712 --> 00:06:54.180
That's it!

00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:55.982
Yusei's in there.

00:06:55.982 --> 00:06:57.550
Now, get us
up there.

00:06:57.550 --> 00:07:00.320
♪

00:07:00.320 --> 00:07:02.222
(Mina)
I feel it's my duty
to tell you that

00:07:02.222 --> 00:07:04.958
it's dangerous to stand
up in a moving vehicle.

00:07:04.958 --> 00:07:06.927
(Akiza)
What about having no
one behind the wheel?

00:07:06.927 --> 00:07:08.561
-Is that dangerous?
-Huh?

00:07:08.561 --> 00:07:11.164
It's speeding up, it--

00:07:11.164 --> 00:07:12.799
Just stay on it.

00:07:12.799 --> 00:07:14.634
I'm gettin' him
outta there.

00:07:14.634 --> 00:07:17.737
♪

00:07:17.737 --> 00:07:19.706
What's this
burning about?

00:07:19.706 --> 00:07:22.475
♪

00:07:22.475 --> 00:07:26.413
Rose Tentacles ought
to do the trick!

00:07:26.413 --> 00:07:28.748
Time to break
Yusei out!

00:07:28.748 --> 00:07:31.685
♪

00:07:31.685 --> 00:07:33.954
(banging)
Huh?

00:07:33.954 --> 00:07:35.255
Who could that be?

00:07:35.255 --> 00:07:38.191
♪

00:07:38.191 --> 00:07:40.126
What's that noise?

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:43.330
♪

00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:45.365
Should I be
concerned right now?

00:07:45.365 --> 00:07:46.533
No, it's fine.

00:07:46.533 --> 00:07:49.302
Controlling my powers
is not an issue anymore.

00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:52.138
♪

00:07:52.138 --> 00:07:53.506
Akiza?

00:07:53.506 --> 00:07:56.109
Hey, did someone in
there order a rescue?

00:07:56.109 --> 00:07:57.143
Who's she?

00:07:57.143 --> 00:07:59.512
A pizza delivery girl--
how should I know?

00:07:59.512 --> 00:08:00.780
I'm just
sayin', boss.

00:08:00.780 --> 00:08:02.449
It might be time to
move on to Plan D.

00:08:02.449 --> 00:08:05.685
D: 'If We Can't Have Him,
Nobody Can' Plan.

00:08:05.685 --> 00:08:06.720
Well...

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:10.023
He has seen my
face now... do it!

00:08:10.023 --> 00:08:11.291
Sweet.

00:08:11.291 --> 00:08:18.531
♪

00:08:18.531 --> 00:08:22.535
Speed it up!

00:08:22.535 --> 00:08:26.272
I do hope that you enjoy a
little deep sea diving, Yusei.

00:08:26.272 --> 00:08:28.041
Shake off
that plant!

00:08:28.041 --> 00:08:32.812
♪

00:08:32.812 --> 00:08:35.248
Mina, try
and get closer!

00:08:35.248 --> 00:08:37.817
(grunting)

00:08:37.817 --> 00:08:39.152
Yusei!

00:08:39.152 --> 00:08:46.459
♪

00:08:46.459 --> 00:08:47.961
Akiza!

00:08:47.961 --> 00:08:56.536
♪

00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.671
Oh well, there
goes our ride...

00:08:58.671 --> 00:09:00.507
I thought the idea
was to get me out.

00:09:00.507 --> 00:09:02.242
Fine, next time,
I won't try to save you,

00:09:02.242 --> 00:09:03.343
I'll just leave you--

00:09:03.343 --> 00:09:07.147
♪

00:09:07.147 --> 00:09:09.482
So, do you think they'll
slow down and let us off?

00:09:09.482 --> 00:09:11.084
Probably not...

00:09:11.084 --> 00:09:12.986
Time for a
different approach.

00:09:12.986 --> 00:09:16.623
♪

00:09:16.623 --> 00:09:19.592
This is Chief of Special
Investigations Mina Simington.

00:09:19.592 --> 00:09:21.895
Security dispatch,
are you receiving this?

00:09:21.895 --> 00:09:24.798
Please come in, over.

00:09:24.798 --> 00:09:27.033
The signal is
still jammed up.

00:09:27.033 --> 00:09:31.171
♪

00:09:31.171 --> 00:09:32.906
Who could
that've been?

00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:42.382
♪

00:09:42.382 --> 00:09:43.650
(Akiza)
Uh-uh, no way.

00:09:43.650 --> 00:09:44.818
Forget about it.

00:09:44.818 --> 00:09:46.086
You are not serious.

00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:47.554
(Yusei)
I hope you like red.

00:09:47.554 --> 00:09:49.823
There's no way.

00:09:49.823 --> 00:09:51.091
You got another plan?

00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:52.725
Yeah, we let
this play out.

00:09:52.725 --> 00:09:54.394
We find out who's
behind all of this.

00:09:54.394 --> 00:09:55.728
Not now we don't.

00:09:55.728 --> 00:09:58.765
You've already put yourself
in enough danger because of me.

00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:01.201
Oh, so riding double
is perfectly--

00:10:01.201 --> 00:10:03.603
We don't have time to
argue about this, Akiza.

00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:05.305
C'mon, hurry
up and hop on.

00:10:05.305 --> 00:10:06.172
Forget it!

00:10:06.172 --> 00:10:07.607
Not gonna happen!

00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:10.176
♪

00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:11.544
Hold on as tight
as you can.

00:10:11.544 --> 00:10:13.279
Okay, look, fine,
I'll admit it,

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:15.381
I've never ridden a Duel
Runner before, okay?

00:10:15.381 --> 00:10:17.383
I have a thing with
super-fast moving objects,

00:10:17.383 --> 00:10:19.419
especially when I'm on
them, it's not what I'd--
Here we go!

00:10:19.419 --> 00:10:20.887
(Akiza)
Oh boy.

00:10:20.887 --> 00:10:23.022
♪

00:10:23.022 --> 00:10:24.290
(Yusei)
What's up with this?

00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:28.361
Reinforcements?

00:10:28.361 --> 00:10:30.964
Come forth,
Yusei Fudo!

00:10:30.964 --> 00:10:34.100
Come forth
and duel me!

00:10:34.100 --> 00:10:35.201
Great.

00:10:35.201 --> 00:10:37.203
This day keeps
getting better.

00:10:37.203 --> 00:10:41.174
♪

00:10:41.174 --> 00:10:42.575
So what are you
gonna do?

00:10:42.575 --> 00:10:44.677
I don't think we have
a whole lot of options.

00:10:44.677 --> 00:10:46.012
Hang on!

00:10:46.012 --> 00:11:03.263
♪

00:11:06.733 --> 00:11:20.013
♪

00:11:20.013 --> 00:11:21.381
(computer voice)
<i>Duel mode engaged.</i>

00:11:21.381 --> 00:11:23.183
<i>Auto-pilot activated.</i>

00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:38.798
♪

00:11:38.798 --> 00:11:40.600
You have sprung
from the frying pan

00:11:40.600 --> 00:11:43.703
only to land in
<i>le flambé,</i> Yusei Fudo!

00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:45.071
I have come
to duel you.

00:11:45.071 --> 00:11:46.339
What are you
talking about?

00:11:46.339 --> 00:11:47.974
Why should
I duel you?

00:11:47.974 --> 00:11:50.543
You do not have
a choice, Yusei Fudo.

00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:53.112
Your Runner has
been tinkered with.

00:11:53.112 --> 00:11:55.415
Should you stop while
in duel mode, it will--

00:11:55.415 --> 00:11:58.117
How you say--
explode, go boom.

00:11:58.117 --> 00:11:59.419
Are you serious?

00:11:59.419 --> 00:12:00.587
No way!

00:12:00.587 --> 00:12:04.290
The only way out
is in, Monsieur Fudo.

00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:05.658
So who are you?

00:12:05.658 --> 00:12:07.894
Are you with the bunch
of goons who kidnapped me?

00:12:07.894 --> 00:12:10.363
Who I am is of no
importance right now.

00:12:10.363 --> 00:12:13.566
I activate Le Speed
World 2 field spell!

00:12:13.566 --> 00:12:19.806
♪

00:12:19.806 --> 00:12:23.042
(computer voice)
<i>Formulating cross-town duel</i>
<i>course and awaiting central</i>

00:12:23.042 --> 00:12:26.779
<i>grid authority's official</i>
<i>authorization.</i>

00:12:26.779 --> 00:12:29.949
<i>Authorization</i>
<i>has been granted.</i>

00:12:29.949 --> 00:12:32.452
<i>A Turbo Duel is</i>
<i>about to commence.</i>

00:12:32.452 --> 00:12:35.188
<i>Combat Lane</i>
<i>transfiguration underway.</i>

00:12:35.188 --> 00:12:37.290
<i>All non-dueling</i>
<i>vehicles must vacate</i>

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:39.692
<i>the Combat Lane</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

00:12:39.692 --> 00:12:53.239
♪

00:12:53.239 --> 00:12:55.441
You're gonna
duel this guy?

00:12:55.441 --> 00:12:56.909
Yeah, I don't like it,
either,

00:12:56.909 --> 00:12:59.712
but he hasn't exactly
given me much of a choice.

00:12:59.712 --> 00:13:01.214
Are you ready?

00:13:01.214 --> 00:13:02.949
Let's Duel!

00:13:02.949 --> 00:13:04.717
(Yusei)
I can't stop to
let you off, Akiza,

00:13:04.717 --> 00:13:06.452
so uh... hang on.

00:13:06.452 --> 00:13:07.820
(Akiza)
Don't worry
about me.

00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:09.589
Just concentrate
on knocking this jerk

00:13:09.589 --> 00:13:11.257
into the next
dimension.

00:13:11.257 --> 00:13:14.394
The first
move is mine!

00:13:14.394 --> 00:13:19.332
I summon Sacred Knight's
Spearholder in defense mode!

00:13:19.332 --> 00:13:21.668
And by placing
one card facedown,

00:13:21.668 --> 00:13:23.836
I defer to you,
Monsieur Fudo.

00:13:23.836 --> 00:13:27.473
Well, aren't
you polite.

00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:30.643
I summon Speed Warrior
in attack mode!

00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:33.279
♪

00:13:33.279 --> 00:13:35.948
Due to its special ability,
Speed Warrior's attack points

00:13:35.948 --> 00:13:37.350
are doubled during
the battle phase

00:13:37.350 --> 00:13:39.252
of the turn it
was summoned!

00:13:39.252 --> 00:13:41.821
So now Speed Warrior,
attack Spearholder

00:13:41.821 --> 00:13:43.790
with Hyper
Sonic Slash!

00:13:43.790 --> 00:13:47.493
(man)
Alas and alack, Yusei Fudo,
I reveal my trap card,

00:13:47.493 --> 00:13:48.995
Floral Shield!

00:13:48.995 --> 00:13:50.430
This negates your
monster's attack,

00:13:50.430 --> 00:13:52.799
and allows me to
draw one card!

00:13:52.799 --> 00:13:54.667
Hope you like
the flowers.

00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:57.837
Looks like my game
is in full bloom.

00:13:57.837 --> 00:14:02.709
♪

00:14:02.709 --> 00:14:06.012
I place three cards
facedown and end my turn.

00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:07.947
♪

00:14:07.947 --> 00:14:09.515
It's your move, buddy.

00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:10.616
<i>Merci.</i>

00:14:10.616 --> 00:14:13.386
♪

00:14:13.386 --> 00:14:15.988
I summon Horse of
the Floral Knights!

00:14:15.988 --> 00:14:19.892
♪

00:14:19.892 --> 00:14:22.295
(computer voice)
<i>When the monster card</i>
<i>Horse of the Floral Knights</i>

00:14:22.295 --> 00:14:24.764
<i>is successfully</i>
<i>summoned to the field,</i>

00:14:24.764 --> 00:14:28.067
<i>you are allowed to draw</i>
<i>one card from your deck.</i>

00:14:28.067 --> 00:14:30.670
And now with the power
of this card in play,

00:14:30.670 --> 00:14:34.807
my strategy shall truly
begin to blossom.

00:14:34.807 --> 00:14:38.344
I activate the Overboost
speed spell!

00:14:38.344 --> 00:14:40.480
This little zinger
of a spell increases

00:14:40.480 --> 00:14:44.751
my Speed Counters by 4 for
the remainder of my turn.

00:14:44.751 --> 00:14:49.322
Try to keep up,
Monsieur Fudo!

00:14:49.322 --> 00:14:51.657
He's increased his speed
in just two turns.

00:14:51.657 --> 00:14:54.260
Whoever this guy is, he sure
knows what he's doing.

00:14:54.260 --> 00:14:57.096
He's a real
Turbo Duelist.

00:14:57.096 --> 00:14:59.165
♪

00:14:59.165 --> 00:15:01.801
Next, I activate the
Speed Fusion Speed Spell,

00:15:01.801 --> 00:15:03.569
which, because of
my current speed,

00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:06.973
allows me to summon to
the field a Fusion Monster!

00:15:06.973 --> 00:15:10.109
By fusing Sacred Knight's
Spearholder and Horse of

00:15:10.109 --> 00:15:15.214
the Floral Knights together,
I can summon, Centaur Mina!

00:15:15.214 --> 00:15:18.484
♪

00:15:18.484 --> 00:15:21.287
And now Centaur
Mina, charge!

00:15:23.890 --> 00:15:27.260
I reveal my trap card,
Scrap-Iron Scarecrow!

00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:29.929
This trap card can negate
your monster's attack.

00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:33.566
Ha-- But I activate
Centaur Mina's special ability,

00:15:33.566 --> 00:15:35.134
which forces your
trap card back

00:15:35.134 --> 00:15:38.671
into the facedown position,
so, I negate your negating.

00:15:38.671 --> 00:15:40.239
Uh-oh.

00:15:40.239 --> 00:15:43.309
<i>Vive La Revolution,</i>
Centaur Mina!

00:15:43.309 --> 00:15:45.044
Continue the charge!

00:15:45.044 --> 00:15:47.580
Attack with
Graceful Blade!

00:15:47.580 --> 00:15:51.217
♪

00:15:51.217 --> 00:15:53.753
Are you doin' okay
back there, Akiza?

00:15:53.753 --> 00:15:54.987
Yeah...

00:15:54.987 --> 00:15:56.322
This feeling...

00:15:56.322 --> 00:15:57.857
I was scared
at first, but,

00:15:57.857 --> 00:16:00.026
something about
the wind and the speed.

00:16:00.026 --> 00:16:01.394
I've never felt
anything like it.

00:16:01.394 --> 00:16:03.362
It's kind of amazing...

00:16:03.362 --> 00:16:06.566
This whole Turbo Duel
thing is a major rush.

00:16:06.566 --> 00:16:09.569
I place one card facedown
and end my turn.

00:16:09.569 --> 00:16:13.773
And now, Overboost fades
away like the morning mist...

00:16:13.773 --> 00:16:16.709
So my Speed Counters
decrease back to 1.

00:16:16.709 --> 00:16:19.612
♪

00:16:19.612 --> 00:16:21.214
It's my turn now!

00:16:21.214 --> 00:16:22.615
♪

00:16:22.615 --> 00:16:26.152
I summon Junk Synchron
in attack mode!

00:16:26.152 --> 00:16:27.887
♪

00:16:27.887 --> 00:16:30.189
And that's not all
I'm busting out!

00:16:30.189 --> 00:16:32.258
'Cause when Junk
Synchron is summoned,

00:16:32.258 --> 00:16:34.193
I can summon one
Level 2-or-below monster

00:16:34.193 --> 00:16:36.629
from my graveyard to
join it on the field!

00:16:36.629 --> 00:16:38.397
I summon
Speed Warrior!

00:16:38.397 --> 00:16:41.901
♪

00:16:41.901 --> 00:16:44.971
And now I tune my Junk
Synchron with my Speed Warrior

00:16:44.971 --> 00:16:48.808
in order to Synchro
Summon Junk Warrior!

00:16:48.808 --> 00:16:58.217
♪

00:16:58.217 --> 00:17:00.553
Let's rev it up!

00:17:00.553 --> 00:17:07.693
♪

00:17:07.693 --> 00:17:10.930
And now Junk Warrior
take out Centaur Mina!

00:17:12.999 --> 00:17:15.334
Go Scrap Fist!

00:17:15.334 --> 00:17:16.569
Not so fast!

00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:18.404
I reveal my trap,
Fleur Guard!

00:17:18.404 --> 00:17:19.906
This prevents you
from destroying

00:17:19.906 --> 00:17:22.575
my monster in battle.

00:17:22.575 --> 00:17:24.644
♪

00:17:24.644 --> 00:17:29.315
You may have saved her, but
you're still takin' damage!

00:17:29.315 --> 00:17:32.585
I end my turn by placing
one card facedown.

00:17:32.585 --> 00:17:35.254
They're perfectly anticipating
each other's moves.

00:17:35.254 --> 00:17:38.224
It's like they share a bond
as duelists or something,

00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:41.694
like they already know each
other without ever having met.

00:17:41.694 --> 00:17:43.596
(Yusei)
Something isn't
right here, Akiza.

00:17:43.596 --> 00:17:46.165
This guy can't be with
the goons who kidnapped me.

00:17:46.165 --> 00:17:48.200
His whole vibe
is different...

00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:53.139
In fact, I think he's
working all on his own...

00:17:53.139 --> 00:17:54.740
It is my turn!

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:56.676
♪

00:17:56.676 --> 00:18:00.580
I summon the Fleur
Synchron Tuner Monster!

00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:02.481
♪

00:18:02.481 --> 00:18:03.916
I know what
this means...

00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:04.850
What is it, Yusei?

00:18:04.850 --> 00:18:05.985
Something bad?

00:18:05.985 --> 00:18:08.487
Look, whatever happens,
just hang on tight.

00:18:08.487 --> 00:18:11.857
(man)
Now it's my turn for
a Synchro Summon...

00:18:11.857 --> 00:18:14.894
I tune Fleur Synchron
with Centaur Mina.

00:18:14.894 --> 00:18:18.230
In order to bring out
Fleur de Chevalier!

00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:29.375
♪

00:18:29.375 --> 00:18:31.444
And now since Fleur
Synchron was used

00:18:31.444 --> 00:18:33.512
to perform
a Synchro Summon,

00:18:33.512 --> 00:18:37.216
I can summon an additional
monster from my hand.

00:18:37.216 --> 00:18:40.553
Say hello to
Apprentice Knight!

00:18:40.553 --> 00:18:43.623
♪

00:18:43.623 --> 00:18:46.659
My Scrap-Iron Scarecrow is
still facedown on my field.

00:18:46.659 --> 00:18:49.729
This guy's well-aware of that,
so I don't think he'll try

00:18:49.729 --> 00:18:53.265
an outright attack
with that Knight, but...

00:18:53.265 --> 00:18:56.068
I can't wait to see
what he does next.

00:18:56.068 --> 00:18:56.902
Is...

00:18:56.902 --> 00:18:58.938
Is Yusei having fun?

00:18:58.938 --> 00:19:02.008
Fleur de Chevalier,
attack Junk Warrior!

00:19:02.008 --> 00:19:04.210
(Yusei)
He must have a trick
up his sleeve.

00:19:04.210 --> 00:19:06.612
And unless Yusei has
a trick of his own,

00:19:06.612 --> 00:19:08.481
this duel is over!

00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:13.853
♪

00:19:16.989 --> 00:19:22.428
♪

00:19:22.428 --> 00:19:27.333
Fleur de Chevalier,
attack Junk Warrior!

00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:29.435
Go Scrap-Iron
Scarecrow!

00:19:29.435 --> 00:19:32.004
This trap deflects
your monster's attack.

00:19:32.004 --> 00:19:34.273
I was hoping you
would try that again,

00:19:34.273 --> 00:19:37.343
for not only can Chevalier
negate your little Scarecrow's

00:19:37.343 --> 00:19:41.847
effect, it can send it to the
great cornfield in the sky!

00:19:41.847 --> 00:19:44.083
That's not good.

00:19:44.083 --> 00:19:46.752
(man)
And with your little
Scarecrow out of the picture,

00:19:46.752 --> 00:19:49.922
Chevalier can vanquish
Junk Warrior.

00:19:49.922 --> 00:19:51.924
<i>En garde,</i> Yusei Fudo!

00:19:51.924 --> 00:19:54.694
♪

00:19:54.694 --> 00:19:56.262
Nicely played.

00:19:56.262 --> 00:19:59.999
But now I know what surprises
your Chevalier has in store.

00:19:59.999 --> 00:20:01.634
<i>Pardonnez-moi?</i>

00:20:01.634 --> 00:20:05.304
I activate my trap
card Miracle's Wake!

00:20:05.304 --> 00:20:07.306
With this card, I can
resurrect a monster

00:20:07.306 --> 00:20:09.041
that was destroyed
this turn.

00:20:09.041 --> 00:20:12.278
So I'm bringing back
Junk Warrior!

00:20:12.278 --> 00:20:18.751
♪

00:20:18.751 --> 00:20:20.553
It appears you were
simply baiting me

00:20:20.553 --> 00:20:23.422
so that you could
learn my strategies...

00:20:23.422 --> 00:20:26.425
<i>Très bon,</i>
Monsieur Fudo.

00:20:26.425 --> 00:20:27.760
Huh?

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:33.766
♪

00:20:33.766 --> 00:20:36.302
I hope this
doesn't hurt.

00:20:36.302 --> 00:20:38.637
If we stop,
the engine will blow!

00:20:38.637 --> 00:20:42.208
♪

00:20:42.208 --> 00:20:43.876
When do we blow up?

00:20:43.876 --> 00:20:45.111
We don't.

00:20:45.111 --> 00:20:46.779
So what's with
the bluff?

00:20:46.779 --> 00:20:48.514
Who are you?

00:20:48.514 --> 00:20:53.986
♪

00:20:53.986 --> 00:20:56.355
My name is
Sherry Leblanc.

00:20:56.355 --> 00:21:00.059
And I wanted to test
your courage under fire.

00:21:00.059 --> 00:21:02.595
You're a... woman
Turbo Duelist?

00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:04.897
(Sherry)
You have passed
the test.

00:21:04.897 --> 00:21:06.799
I shall dispense with
the games and tell you

00:21:06.799 --> 00:21:09.568
the true nature
of my intentions.

00:21:09.568 --> 00:21:12.938
I have sought you out so that
I might steal you for my own.

00:21:12.938 --> 00:21:16.008
♪

